ChatGPT said:

If you want to replace your onClick + router.push approach with Next.js <Link>, it’s actually simpler and more semantic. Here’s how you can do it:

Using next/link
import Link from "next/link";

export default function CompanyButton({ company }) {
  return (
    <Link href={`/company/${company.id}`}>
      <button className="bg-blue-500 text-white font-semibold px-8 py-4 hover:bg-blue-700 cursor-pointer">
        View Details
      </button>
    </Link>
  );
}


Notes:

href is where you want to navigate.

The <button> inside <Link> works fine for styling, but if you want, you can also style the <Link> directly as a block element.

No need for router.push or a separate navigate function.